data.enText: to move slowly from side to side; to move sth in this way
The branches were swaying in the wind.

data.chText: 他们伴着音乐扭动屁股，有节奏地跳舞。
data.enText: They danced rhythmically, swaying their hips to the music.
to persuade sb to believe sth or do sth

data.chText: 他相貌不凡，谈吐风趣，但她不为所动。
data.enText: She wasn't swayed by his good looks or his clever talk.
a movement from side to side

data.chText: 统治；势力；支配；控制；影响
该岛很大一部分控制在叛军手里。
data.enText: Rebel forces hold sway over much of the island.

data.chText: 他毫不犹豫地利用受他控制的那些人。
data.enText: He was quick to exploit those who fell under his sway .

ex.chText: 小船随波浪左右摇摆，她觉得很恶心。
ex.enText: She felt sick as the waves rocked the boat from side to side.

ex.chText: 他把儿子抱在怀里轻轻摇晃。
ex.enText: He gently rocked his son in his arms.

ex.chText: 树枝在微风中轻轻摆动。
ex.enText: The branches swayed gently in the breeze.

ex.chText: 那个虚弱的男孩子摇晃着倒下了。
ex.enText: That feeble boy swayed and fell.

synonyms.bx: 指不稳定或灵活的东西来回晃动，如树木、枝叶等。

ex.chText: 只有一块指示牌在风中摇摆。
ex.enText: There is only one sign swinging in the wind.

ex.chText: 他妈妈让他不要把包前后晃来晃去。
ex.enText: His mother asked him not to swing his bag back and forth.

synonyms.bx: 指某物一端固定，另一端来回摆动。

tr: move back and forth or sideways
example: She rocked back and forth on her feet

tr: cause to move back and forth
example: the wind swayed the trees gently

tr: move or walk in a swinging or swaying manner

example: His speech did not sway the voters

value.def: When people or things sway, they lean or swing slowly from one side to the other.

example.ex: The people swayed back and forth with arms linked...
example.tran: 人们手挽手，前后摇晃着。

example.ex: The whole boat swayed and tipped.
...a coastal highway lined with tall, swaying palm trees.
example.tran: 两旁有摇曳的高大棕榈树的沿海公路

value.def: If you are swayed by someone or something, you are influenced by them.

example.ex: Don't ever be swayed by fashion.
example.tran: 永远不要受潮流的影响。

example.ex: ...last minute efforts by the main political parties to sway the voters in tomorrow's local elections.
example.tran: 主要政党为说服选民在明天的地方选举中投自己一票而作出的最后努力

value.def: If someone or something holds sway, they have great power or influence over a particular place or activity.

example.ex: South of the Usk, a completely different approach seems to hold sway...
example.tran: 阿斯克以南盛行的似乎是一种完全不同的方式。

example.ex: The 'families' are the basic units, each holding sway over a recognised territory.
example.tran: “家庭”是基本单位，每一个家庭都控制着自己受人认可的领地。

value.tran: 占统治地位;具有重大影响力

value.def: If you are under the sway of someone or something, they have great influence over you.

example.ex: How mothers keep daughters under their sway is the subject of the next five sections.
example.tran: 在接下来的 5 节将探讨母亲怎样管教女儿。

value.tran: 在…的控制下;在…的支配下;在…的影响下

trans: 在…的控制下;在…的支配下;在…的影响下
占统治地位;具有重大影响力
